<br>
And hey, if enough people really want high res models, they can just sell an expansion pack and suck more money out of you later. Hah.<br>
<br>
Will the absence of high res models deter people from buying it? Probably, but realistically, do you think it's enough to cause a dent in profits? Probably not. It's Blizzard after all. Who the fuck cares. <br>
<br>
I'll be trying it like everything else, but I mostly hope they get a good chat and trade interface going on. EQ's is rock solid of how I want all these MMORPGs to emulate right down to all the commands. It works so god damn well. I'm not talking about the XML skinning, either. I'm talking about the functionality of channels, tells, and commands implemented. And the fact multiple windows can be made and moved around.<br>
